<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>7.3 Liter Diesel Engine Service (1991) - VALVE TRAIN: CAMSHAFT, HYDRAULIC VALVE LIFTERS AND PUSH RODS -
        CAMSHAFT ASSEMBLY - REMOVAL
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="3">
        <title>REMOVAL</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Prior to camshaft removal, mount dial indicator on front of engine and check and record
                camshaft gear-to-crankshaft gear backlash (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350408">4.8</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ). If backlash exceeds specified limits (see
                <hotlnk document="e435_HL4350401.xml" xrefid="hl4350401">"SPECIFICATIONS"</hotlnk>) timing gears should
                be replaced.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the dial indicator tip @ a gear tooth and remove lash.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Zero the dial indicator.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Move the gear by hand and read the indicator. Record backlash.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Reposition the dial indicator and check camshaft end play (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350409">4.9</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ) as follows:
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Push the camshaft toward the rear of the engine.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Zero the dial indicator.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position a large screwdriver between the camshaft gear and the block. Pull the camshaft
                forward and release it. Compare the dial indicator reading with the specifications.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the dial indicator.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If end play exceeds specified limits, (see
                <hotlnk document="e435_HL4350401.xml" xrefid="hl4350401">"SPECIFICATIONS"</hotlnk>), replace the
                camshaft thrust plate.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove camshaft Allen screw and washer,
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350410">4.10</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
            <figure id="ef4350408" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg11153" filename="../figcg1/CG11153.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 4.8 Camshaft Gear-to-Crankshaft Gear Backlash Measurement</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef4350409" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg11154" filename="../figcg1/CG11154.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 4.9 Checking Camshaft End Play</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef4350410" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg11155" filename="../figcg1/CG11155.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 4.10 Removing Camshaft Allen Screw [Earlier Cam Gear Shown]</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove camshaft thrust plate bolts through the access holes,
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e435_72.xml" xrefid="ef4350411">4.11</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With the camshaft thrust plate bolts and camshaft Allen screw removed, use
                <emph type="bold">ZTSE1880-D</emph>
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e435_72.xml" xrefid="ef4350412">4.12</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                (earlier gear shown) to remove the camshaft assembly. When the remover and adapter are threaded into the
                camshaft, proper leverage is provided for easy camshaft assembly removal.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>ZTSE1880-D consists of:</para>
                    <randlist type="bullet">
                        <item>
                            <para>ZTSE1880-1 Camshaft Remover and Installer</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>ZTSE1880-2 Adapter</para>
                        </item>
                    </randlist>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
